00:08:11,853 --> 00:08:15,176
Let's talk through it a little bit. On the right-hand side, you can see each of these

143
00:08:15,216 --> 00:08:19,119
gems are coming down on a unique string, meaning you'd have to strum that string when it reaches

144
00:08:19,159 --> 00:08:23,282
the bar at the bottom. And then there's a light on it that tells you relative position

145
00:08:23,342 --> 00:08:26,845
of actually which fret you'd have to hit. Kind of confusing. On the left-hand side,

146
00:08:27,065 --> 00:08:31,769
there's the idea of what a chord could look like in this. We still haven't quite nailed

147
00:08:31,789 --> 00:08:37,053
that. Then we put this into video. This is an actual song in motion. There's no sound

148
00:08:37,093 --> 00:08:37,454
on this one.

