00:08:41,449 --> 00:08:43,469
And this is kind of scary for us.

151
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:45,910
We were happy to try string relative,

152
00:08:45,950 --> 00:08:47,610
but that wasn't maybe super successful.

153
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,430
But then we got to this one right here.

154
00:08:50,231 --> 00:08:51,871
This came towards the end of our period here.

155
00:08:51,891 --> 00:08:54,991
And you can see, like, with that same real data we had before,

156
00:08:55,051 --> 00:08:56,392
this is looking a lot more promising.

157
00:08:56,792 --> 00:08:58,532
This is actually closer to what we end up with.

158
00:08:59,092 --> 00:09:01,173
Chords aren't quite figured out, but notes

159
00:09:01,793 --> 00:09:03,533
and their relative positions are a little bit easier

