00:44:15,482 --> 00:44:19,822
When I first came to Harmonics, I was really surprised by how much polish went into the tiny elements of the game.

844
00:44:19,842 --> 00:44:21,743
I'm just going to talk about one tiny little example here.

845
00:44:22,503 --> 00:44:27,864
So, for a series of repeated chords, you can see it from the old prototype video,

846
00:44:28,804 --> 00:44:30,864
we would have names for every single chord,

847
00:44:31,204 --> 00:44:34,945
and it would be kind of intimidating and hard to tell when your chord changed.

848
00:44:35,525 --> 00:44:41,486
So, one of the first things we did is do a little bright highlight on the first chord in a series of chords.

849
00:44:41,546 --> 00:44:43,847
So, every time the chord changed, you would see a little bit of a pop.

850
00:44:44,587 --> 00:44:49,090
And we eliminated the chord name next to the chord of anything but the very first chord.

851
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:54,275
Doing that, of course, meant that after the very first chord, it would scroll off screen.

852
00:44:54,715 --> 00:44:58,939
So what we did was we locked it into place until that series of chords is gone.

853
00:44:59,259 --> 00:45:04,483
So if you do use the chord name, then it doesn't go away and you know a series of 50 chords

854
00:45:04,543 --> 00:45:05,344
is still this chord.

855
00:45:06,865 --> 00:45:09,648
At this time, we were also able to get in a ton of our wishlist items.

856
00:45:09,788 --> 00:45:10,748
Here's just a small sample.

857
00:45:11,189 --> 00:45:13,691
We finally nailed the arpeggio look and got it working in the game.

858
00:45:14,240 --> 00:45:17,021
We got guitar techniques such as slides up and down the neck

859
00:45:17,101 --> 00:45:19,041
and muted notes, which are just playing

860
00:45:19,081 --> 00:45:19,961
without actually fretting.

861
00:45:21,422 --> 00:45:23,762
And hammer-ons and pull-offs and tons more.

862
00:45:24,162 --> 00:45:26,923
One last example was this idea of being

863
00:45:26,943 --> 00:45:28,723
able to turn on the chord numbering

