00:45:34,524 --> 00:45:36,585
a rendering bug that didn't let us get to this

868
00:45:36,625 --> 00:45:37,625
until the very last day.

869
00:45:38,245 --> 00:45:40,645
And with a lot of begging on my part for the producers,

870
00:45:40,765 --> 00:45:41,645
we actually got this in.

871
00:45:43,806 --> 00:45:43,926
So.

872
00:45:44,861 --> 00:45:48,244
Our summary here is, when we go from prototype to production,

873
00:45:48,524 --> 00:45:49,505
it always takes us a lot longer.

874
00:45:49,545 --> 00:45:51,907
We haven't quite nailed it, but for this project,

875
00:45:53,908 --> 00:45:54,829
we did a couple techniques.

876
00:45:55,169 --> 00:45:57,531
For one, we used placeholder content

877
00:45:58,532 --> 00:46:00,233
for being able to rapidly develop.

878
00:46:01,134 --> 00:46:02,555
We learned a lot from these MP3s,

879
00:46:02,635 --> 00:46:04,897
and we learned a lot about the space,

880
00:46:04,937 --> 00:46:06,739
just like we did earlier on with the pictures and the video.

881
00:46:08,760 --> 00:46:10,402
We revisited our target audience,

882
00:46:10,442 --> 00:46:11,743
and that helped our team.

883
00:46:12,846 --> 00:46:17,629
realign on the core goals that we should really be working on before we think of the bigger issues, or the smaller issues.

884
00:46:18,430 --> 00:46:23,793
And finally, short term deadlines helped us get our work done faster as people wanted to see the results of that work,

885
00:46:24,374 --> 00:46:26,155
especially stuff like external play tests.

886
00:46:27,476 --> 00:46:31,539
So, we're really happy with the response from Pro Guitar and Rock Band 3.

